Description: Fragment of shoulder and turn to neck of East Greek black-figured pottery dinos; interior: black glaze on inside of rim, more streaky glaze on shoulder; exterior: fillet below lost rim black (traces only remaining); on shoulder, black-figure decoration consisting of head and paw of lion to left, with mouth open, added red tongue and three added white dots on neck and possibly some red on neck, attacking uncertain adversary, to right.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1208) (Phase 1)
